## Theme 1: Observability & Telemetry (15 PRs)

> Backbone for operating OmniRoute at scale. Directly addresses #4252 (undici 502 bursts with no trace), #4262 (confusing prompt-cache/usage reporting), #4771/#4623 (OOM without metrics), and #4608 (Aliyun WAF — no audit trail).

---

### PR-001

**Title**: OpenTelemetry SDK bootstrap with OTLP/gRPC and OTLP/HTTP exporters
**Problem**: OmniRoute's `src/instrumentation.ts` and `src/instrumentation-node.ts` exist but there is no first-class OpenTelemetry pipeline. Operators cannot trace a 5xx burst to a specific executor or upstream call. With 160+ providers and live issues like #4252 (intermittent 502s from undici) and #4608 (Aliyun WAF blocking), root-causing is currently impossible without Wireshark.
**Solution**:
- Architecture: Introduce `src/lib/observability/otel.ts` providing a single `initTelemetry(config)` function used by both `src/instrumentation.ts` and `src/instrumentation-node.ts`. Configure an OTLP exporter (gRPC + HTTP fallback) with auto-detection from env vars `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`, `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME`, `OTEL_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTES`. Bundle `@opentelemetry/api`, `@opentelemetry/sdk-node`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http`, `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-grpc`, `@opentelemetry/resources`, `@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions` as direct deps.
- Add a no-op default (when `OTEL_SDK_DISABLED=true`) so Electron-PWA users pay nothing.
- Files affected: `src/instrumentation.ts:1-40`, `src/instrumentation-node.ts:1-60` (entry), `src/lib/observability/otel.ts` (new, 220 LOC), `src/lib/observability/resource.ts` (new, 80 LOC), `src/lib/observability/index.ts` (new barrel), `package.json:100-180` (new deps), `.env.example:1-30`, `tests/unit/observability/otel.test.ts` (new, 180 LOC), `docs/observability/01-quickstart.md` (new, 120 LOC).
**Test plan**: Unit tests mock `@opentelemetry/exporter-trace-otlp-http` to assert spans are exported with correct resource attributes. Integration test boots a fake collector (TestExporter), fires 1000 fake requests, asserts throughput. Confirm zero-overhead when `OTEL_SDK_DISABLED=true` (CPU profile).
**Risk**: Low — feature-flagged; defaults to no-op.
**Estimate**: M

---

### PR-002

**Title**: Auto-instrumentation for Next.js, undici, http, and Express layers
**Problem**: Even with PR-001 in place, spans must be created around the actual hot paths. Today the proxy in `src/proxy.ts:1-200` and the per-executor HTTP calls inside `open-sse/executors/*.ts` are unaudited. This is the reason #4252 and #4608 have remained open: we don't know which executor fails.
**Solution**:
- Register `@opentelemetry/instrumentation-http`, `@opentelemetry/instrumentation-undici`, `@opentelemetry/instrumentation-express`, `@opentelemetry/instrumentation-next`.
- Wrap `src/proxy.ts` with a manual `tracer.startActiveSpan("omniroute.proxy.request", ...)` carrying attributes: `http.method`, `http.route`, `provider.id`, `model.id`, `combo.id`, `tenant.id`, `quota.strategy`, `cache.hit`.
- Wrap each executor in `open-sse/executors/base.ts:1-50` to emit a per-upstream span with `upstream.host`, `upstream.method`, `upstream.status_code`, `upstream.retry_attempt`.
- Files affected: `src/lib/observability/auto.ts` (new, 260 LOC), `src/lib/observability/proxy-span.ts` (new, 110 LOC), `src/proxy.ts:1-200` (instrumented), `open-sse/executors/base.ts:1-50` (instrumented), `package.json:160-220` (new deps), `tests/unit/observability/auto.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC).
**Test plan**: Use `@opentelemetry/sdk-trace-base` `InMemorySpanExporter` to capture spans from a synthetic `/v1/chat/completions` request. Assert that each executor call creates a child span with `upstream.host` and propagates `traceparent` header.
**Risk**: Med — touches all 66 executors' shared base, but only via decorator pattern.
**Estimate**: L

---

### PR-003

**Title**: Prometheus `/metrics` endpoint with HTTP/RED, executor saturation, and quota gauges
**Problem**: Operators have no SLO-grade telemetry. #4771 (heap OOM) was reported without CPU/memory traces; #4623 (instrumentation compile OOM) lacks measurement. Grafana dashboards cannot exist.
**Solution**:
- Architecture: Expose `GET /metrics` in Prometheus text-exposition format (port 20128 by default; gated by `OMNIROUTE_METRICS_ENABLED`).
- Implement metric families: `omniroute_http_requests_total{route,method,status}`, `omniroute_http_request_duration_seconds_bucket{route,method,le}` (histogram), `omniroute_provider_upstream_attempts_total{provider,model,outcome}`, `omniroute_provider_upstream_duration_seconds`, `omniroute_provider_tokens_total{provider,model,direction}`, `omniroute_cache_hits_total{layer}`, `omniroute_cache_misses_total{layer}`, `omniroute_quota_remaining{provider,model}`, `omniroute_process_heap_bytes`, `omniroute_process_resident_bytes`, `omniroute_event_loop_lag_seconds`.
- Files affected: `src/lib/observability/metrics.ts` (new, 380 LOC), `src/lib/observability/registry.ts` (new, 90 LOC), `src/lib/observability/handler.ts` (new, 70 LOC), `src/server-init.ts:1-100` (route mount), `src/app/api/metrics/route.ts` (new, 30 LOC), `src/middleware/metrics-mw.ts` (new, 110 LOC), `package.json:200-260` (add `prom-client`), `tests/unit/observability/metrics.test.ts` (new, 250 LOC), `docs/observability/02-prometheus.md` (new, 100 LOC), `dashboards/omniroute-overview.json` (new Grafana dashboard, 300 LOC JSON).
**Test plan**: Generate 10k fake requests, scrape `/metrics`, parse with `prom-client` and verify counters. Assert that label cardinality is bounded (no `model` explosion from random strings).
**Risk**: Med — label cardinality is a real footgun; add cardinality cap tests.
**Estimate**: L

