### PR-013

**Title**: Bundle-aware tracing — show downsizing/coalescing effectiveness per request
**Problem**: PR-#4268 ("Stacked RTK+Caveman often records no savings") — operators can't see whether compression actually worked for a given request. The compression logic in `src/lib/compression` (RTK + Caveman) lacks per-request feedback.
**Solution**:
- Wrap each compression call with a span carrying `compression.layer`, `tokens.before`, `tokens.after`, `tokens.saved_ratio`, `ms.elapsed`.
- Add metric `omniroute_compression_saved_tokens_total{layer,model}`.
- UI page `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/compression/page.tsx` showing per-model compression effectiveness with stacked bars.
- Files affected: `src/lib/compression/rtk.ts:1-200` (instrumented), `src/lib/compression/caveman.ts:1-200` (instrumented), `src/lib/compression/index.ts:1-80` (instrumented), `src/lib/observability/metrics.ts:1-380` (extend), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/compression/page.tsx` (new, 200 LOC), `src/app/(dashboard)/observability/compression/StackedBar.tsx` (new, 130 LOC), `src/app/api/observability/compression/route.ts` (new, 90 LOC), `tests/unit/observability/compression.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `docs/observability/10-compression.md` (new, 70 LOC).
**Test plan**: Fire 1k prompts of varying length, assert metric sums equal actual saved tokens.
**Risk**: Low.
**Estimate**: M

