## Theme 2: Provider Integrations (20 PRs)

> OmniRoute ships 66 executors in `open-sse/executors/` and supports 160+ provider IDs. These PRs add the most-requested missing adapters and harden existing ones. Each PR ships a fully working executor with tests, fixture capture, schema mapping, model list, and dashboard card.

---

### PR-016

**Title**: AWS Bedrock Converse & ConverseStream with SigV4 signing
**Problem**: A `bedrock.ts` executor exists, but does not implement the Converse API; users on AWS need a native path. SigV4 is currently hand-rolled and breaks for the latest regions.
**Solution**:
- New executor `open-sse/executors/bedrock-converse.ts` (380 LOC) using the Converse/ConverseStream APIs for Claude 3.5/3.7, Llama 3.x, Mistral, and Titan.
- SigV4 via `@aws-sdk/signature-v4` and `@aws-crypto/sha256-js` (instead of `aws4`) for ARM64 compatibility. Honour `AWS_REGION`, `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_SESSION_TOKEN`, plus `OMNIROUTE_BEDROCK_ENDPOINT` for GovCloud.
- Files affected: `open-sse/executors/bedrock-converse.ts` (new, 380 LOC), `open-sse/executors/bedrock.ts:1-200` (kept as legacy), `open-sse/executors/index.ts:1-100` (register), `open-sse/transformer/bedrock.ts` (new, 220 LOC), `src/lib/providers/registry.ts:1-200` (register), `src/shared/providers/bedrock.ts` (new, 110 LOC), `src/shared/types/bedrock.ts` (new, 80 LOC), `tests/unit/executors/bedrock-converse.test.ts` (new, 280 LOC), `tests/integration/executors/bedrock.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `tests/fixtures/bedrock/converse-success.json` (new), `docs/providers/01-bedrock.md` (new, 130 LOC).
**Test plan**: Unit tests use mocked `fetch` to verify SigV4 signature, payload shape. Integration test against a `moto` server.
**Risk**: Med.
**Estimate**: L

