## Theme 5: Developer Experience (10 PRs)

> The community runs `bin/omniroute.mjs` and `src/lib/cliTools` heavily. Several issues (#4252, #4716, #4767) trace to fragile CLI behavior. These PRs harden the surface.

---

### PR-061

**Title**: CLI plugin system — extend `bin/omniroute.mjs` with third-party subcommands
**Problem**: `bin/omniroute.mjs` and `src/lib/cliTools` have ~25 hard-coded commands. Custom commands cannot be added without rebuilding.
**Solution**:
- New module `src/lib/cliTools/plugin.ts` (320 LOC) implementing a small plugin discovery protocol. Plugins live under `~/.omniroute/plugins/<name>/plugin.mjs` and export `{ name, commands: CommandDef[] }`.
- Files affected: `src/lib/cliTools/plugin.ts` (new, 320 LOC), `src/lib/cliTools/discovery.ts` (new, 130 LOC), `src/lib/cliTools/loader.ts` (new, 110 LOC), `bin/omniroute.mjs:1-200` (extend), `src/lib/cliTools/registry.ts:1-180` (integrate), `tests/unit/cliTools/plugin.test.ts` (new, 240 LOC), `tests/integration/cliTools/plugin.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `docs/cli/06-plugins.md` (new, 130 LOC).
**Test plan**: Sample plugin end-to-end via the CLI; assert command appears in `help`.
**Risk**: Low.
**Estimate**: L

---

### PR-062

**Title**: `--dry-run` and `--explain` for every CLI command that mutates state
**Problem**: `omniroute config set`, `omniroute rotate-keys`, and friends can wreck a deployment if a user mistypes.
**Solution**:
- New module `src/lib/cliTools/dryRun.ts` (260 LOC) wrapping the mutating commands with a no-op execution path that prints planned actions.
- Files affected: `src/lib/cliTools/dryRun.ts` (new, 260 LOC), `src/lib/cliTools/explain.ts` (new, 130 LOC), `bin/omniroute.mjs:1-200` (extend), `tests/unit/cliTools/dryRun.test.ts` (new, 240 LOC), `tests/integration/cliTools/dryRun.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `docs/cli/07-dryrun.md` (new, 100 LOC).
**Test plan**: Assert no DB write on `--dry-run`; assert output matches expected.
**Risk**: Low.
**Estimate**: M

---

