### PR-066

**Title**: `omniroute doctor` — diagnose common misconfigurations
**Problem**: Users hit issues that need a human to triage (env vars, port collisions, missing SQLite migrations). No automated diagnosis.
**Solution**:
- New module `src/lib/cliTools/doctor.ts` (320 LOC) running a battery of checks (env, ports, db, disk, mTLS, network to upstream providers). Reports per-check pass/warn/fail with remediation steps.
- Files affected: `src/lib/cliTools/doctor.ts` (new, 320 LOC), `src/lib/cliTools/doctor/checks.ts` (new, 130 LOC), `bin/omniroute-doctor.mjs` (new, 60 LOC), `tests/unit/cliTools/doctor.test.ts` (new, 240 LOC), `tests/integration/cliTools/doctor.test.ts` (new, 200 LOC), `docs/cli/09-doctor.md` (new, 100 LOC).
**Test plan**: Inject failures; assert detection.
**Risk**: Low.
**Estimate**: L

